revision.text:
{{Infobox football tournament season | title = 1963 Norwegian Football Cup | year = | other_title = Norgesmesterskapet i fotball for menn 1963 | image = | imagesize = | caption = | country = {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Football Association of Norway|Norway]] | num_teams = | defending champions = [[SK Gjøvik-Lyn|Gjøvik-Lyn]] | champions = [[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]] (6th title) | runner-up = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]] | matches = | goals = | top goal scorer = | player = | prevseason = [[1962 Norwegian Football Cup|1962]] | nextseason = [[1964 Norwegian Football Cup|1964]] }} The '''1963 [[Norwegian Football Cup]]''' was the first all-Norwegian cup, as it was the first year clubs from [[Northern Norway]] were allowed to participate in the cup. Of the two northern Norwegian teams that participated this year, [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] made it all the way to the fourth round.
The surprise team of the cup this year was [[Sagene IF|Sagene]], a team that made it to the quarter final, despite playing in the third division (tier three).
[[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]] won the cup, beating [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]] 2-1 in the final.
==Final three rounds== {{Round8 <!--Date-Place/Team 1/Score 1/Team 2/Score 2 --> <!--quarter finals --> |25 September - ?, [[Gjøvik]] |'''[[SK Gjøvik-Lyn|Gjøvik-Lyn]]''' <small>([[Extra time|AET]])</small>|'''2''' |[[Sagene IF|Sagene]] |1 |29 September - [[Ullevaal stadion]], [[Oslo]] |[[FK Lyn|Lyn]]|0 |'''[[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]''' |'''5''' |9 October - [[Stavanger stadion]], [[Stavanger]] |'''[[Viking FK|Viking]]''' <small>([[Replay (sports)|Replay]])</small>|'''2''' |[[Frigg Oslo FK|Frigg]]|0 |29 September - [[Fredrikstad stadion]], [[Fredrikstad]] |'''[[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]''' |'''3''' |[[Vålerenga Fotball|Vålerenga]]|0 <!-- semi finals --> |20 October – ?, [[Gjøvik]] |[[SK Gjøvik-Lyn|Gjøvik-Lyn]]|2 |'''[[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]''' |'''3''' |20 October - [[Stavanger stadion]], [[Stavanger]] |[[Viking FK|Viking]] |0 |'''[[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]''' |'''2''' <!--final --> |27 October – [[Ullevaal stadion]], [[Oslo]] |'''[[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]''' <small>([[Extra time|AET]])</small>|'''2''' |[[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]|1 }}
