{{Football club infobox | clubname = Capricorne | image = | fullname = Capricorne FC| nickname = | founded = | ground = [[Stade Maître Kira]], [[Madagascar]]| capacity = | chairman = | manager = | league = [[THB Champions League]] | season = 2013 | position = | }}
'''Capricorne FC''' is a Malagasy football club who currently plays in the [[THB Champions League]] the top division of [[Malagasy Republic|Malagasy]] football.<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/teams/madagascar/asjfc-capricorne/20171/matches/</ref> The team is based in the [[Atsimo-Andrefana]] region in western [[Madagascar]].
==Stadium== Currently the team plays at the 5000 capacity [[Stade Maître Kira]].
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links== *[https://int.soccerway.com/teams/madagascar/asjfc-capricorne/20171/ Soccerway] *[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesm/madag2013.html] [[Category:Football clubs in Madagascar]] {{Madagascar-footyclub-stub}}

{{infobox country at games | NOC = BOT | NOCname = [[Botswana National Olympic Committee]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 1 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Botswana|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=1980|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Botswana]]''' has competed in eight Summer Games. Botswana's first appearance was in the 1980 Summer Olympic Games, in Moscow. They have never competed in the Winter Games. Botswana won its first medal at the 2012 London Olympic games with [[Nijel Amos]] getting a silver in the 800m.
