'''Gene Bissell Field''', in [[Salina, Kansas]], is the home field for the [[Kansas Wesleyan Coyotes|Kansas Wesleyan University Coyotes]] football and soccer teams. The field was named in honor of former head coach [[Franklin Gene Bissell]], who attended the opening day celebration on October 3, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ksal.com/sports/no-21-kwu-wins-opener-at-graves-family-sports-complex/|title=No. 21 KWU Wins Opener at Graves Family Sports Complex|publisher=[[KSAL (AM)|KSAL]]|accessdate=3 January 2016}}</ref>

The field is circled with a collegiate track and includes a grandstand which seats over 1900 spectators. The field is part of the [[Graves Family Sports Complex]], which replaced the demolished Glen Martin Stadium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ksal.com/glenn-martin-stadium-comes-down/|title=Glenn Martin Stadium Comes Down|publisher=[[KSAL (AM)|KSAL]]|accessdate=3 January 2016}}</ref>

