'''Limón Fútbol Club''', commonly known as '''Limón''',  is a professional [[association football|football]] club based in [[Limón]], Costa Rica. It plays in the [[Liga FPD]].

The team play their home matches at the Estadio Juan Gobán, although the more recent Estadio Nuevo de Limón serves as an alternative ground.

==History==
In 2009, local businessman Carlos Howden Pascal decided to invest in local second division soccer team [[Asociacion Deportiva Limonense|A.D. Limonense]], shareholders agreed to lease the team and were renamed "Limón FC".<ref>[http://www.prensalibre.cr/pl/deporte/2944-c100-millones-para-empezar.html PrensaLibre News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104011256/http://www.prensalibre.cr/pl/deporte/2944-c100-millones-para-empezar.html |date=2013-11-04 }}</ref> In 2010, the team quickly returned to Costa Rica top level division Primera Division.
By June 2011, Carlos Pascal was encarcerated and his banks accounts frozen,<ref>[http://www.prensalibre.cr/pl/suceso/44510-detienen-a-presidente-de-limon-fc-por-vinculos-con-mafia-norteamericana.html PrensaLibre News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104025625/http://www.prensalibre.cr/pl/suceso/44510-detienen-a-presidente-de-limon-fc-por-vinculos-con-mafia-norteamericana.html |date=2013-11-04 }}</ref> compromising the team financial situation. In 2013, he was released but his bank accounts were still frozen,<ref>[http://www.prensalibre.cr/lpl/as-deportivo/78743-carlos-pascal-sale-libre-al-ser-absuelto-de-toda-pena-.html PrensaLibre Pascal Released] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20131104102516/http://www.prensalibre.cr/lpl/as-deportivo/78743-carlos-pascal-sale-libre-al-ser-absuelto-de-toda-pena-.html |date=2013-11-04 }}</ref> Currently some players are receiving bonds as salary until the case is settled.<ref>[http://www.nacion.com/deportes/futbol-costa-rica/Aficion-comercio-limonense-unen_0_1374462626.html Nacion.com Players Salary Update]</ref> Many players don't only play for Limón as a job. Most of them work in other places like Ports.

==Honours==
* 2009–10: Segunda Division Champions
* 2012–13: [[2012–13 Costa Rican Primera División season|Invierno Semi-finals]] <ref>[http://www.mariosegura.com/futbol/primera-division-de-costa-rica/15355-semifinales-limon-fc-alajuelense-herediano-saprissa Limon in Semifinals] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104125514/http://www.mariosegura.com/futbol/primera-division-de-costa-rica/15355-semifinales-limon-fc-alajuelense-herediano-saprissa |date=2013-11-04 }}</ref>

